###  http://edugraph.io/edu/Logarithm
:Logarithm rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                    edu:Area ;
           edu:expands :Exponentiation ;
           edu:partOf :ArithmeticOperations ;
           rdfs:isDefinedBy """Finding the exponent to which a base (an integer) must be raised to produce a given integer.

Example: log₃ 81 = 4 because 3 ^ 4 = 81""" .


###  http://edugraph.io/edu/Logic
:Logic rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                edu:Area ;
       rdfs:isDefinedBy "The branch of mathematics that studies reasoning and valid arguments. It provides a framework for determining whether something is true or false based on given premises. It is the foundation for constructing proofs, ensuring that conclusions follow logically from their premises." .


###  http://edugraph.io/edu/LowestCommonDenominator
:LowestCommonDenominator rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                  edu:Area ;
                         edu:partOf :FractionNumbers ;
                         rdfs:isDefinedBy """Finding the smallest common multiple of the denominators of two or more fractions.

Example: The lowest common denominator of 1/4 and 1/6 is 12.""" .


